having a wisdom tooth removed and scared to death i'm having one wisdom tooth removed next monday and i have just found out its going to be done under a local anesthetic i am now terrified i don't like dentists at the best of times and i'm scared of needles i'm not sure how much its going to hurt during the op or after it any advice would be great thanks sall i'm just back right this second from havin ma second one removed i was absolutly cacking it the first time but it was no problems at all the needles can be a bit scary but you dont see them and it's just a little scratch on your gum then within minutes you canny feel a thing all you can feel is them tugging at your tooth but it's not painful in the slightest make sure you take strong painkillers before the numbness wares off though my first one hasnt really been that painful just as sore as a stubbed toe you'll be fine try not to worry its really not that bad and just think what perfect teeth you'll have after remember to keep it clean though x Tooth Dentistry Cocaine Dental caries Anesthesia Analgesic Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Mouth ulcer Epidural Wisdom teeth Dentures Gingivitis Bruxism Childbirth Rich Mullins Carpal tunnel syndrome Menstrual cup Theory of conduct Knife Breastfeeding First aid Halitosis Prostate cancer Crown (dentistry) Glen Jacobs Diving Halloween Oral hygiene Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Avenue Q Grief Sydney Riot of 1879 Clove Methamphetamine Doom enemies Jon Secada Nine Inch Nails The Fairly OddParents Dental brace Social rule Needle aspiration biopsy Final Fantasy magic Obsessive-compulsive disorder -phobia Equine conformation Textile manufacturing Neuropathy Kurt Angle The Inside The Dentist Piccolo Junior Saga My Family (television) Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Fecal incontinence Dialysis Procrastination Ranma __ characters Endocarditis Stomach cancer Dental floss Acupuncture Characters of Naruto Goodness and value theory Shaggy dog s